  </data>
  <data name="AllowMicrosoftFirewallSentinelProfileDescription.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Extends the Default Windows profile to permit network connectivity for applications signed with Microsoft's codesigning certificates. This profile grants access to builtin Windows components and Microsoftsigned software while excluding unsigned or nonMicrosoft thirdparty applications from Internet access.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="SignedAndReputableFirewallSentinelProfileDescription.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Extends the Allow Microsoft profile by permitting everything it allows, and additionally allowing all reputable, signed applications based on Intelligent Security Cloud verdicts. This provides the broadest firewall coverage.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="FirewallSentinelMainTopDescription.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Choose one of the identity-based profiles below to apply. These profiles currently affect outbound traffic only; inbound settings remain unchanged. After you apply a profile, you can expand its rules to allow any third-party applications that require Internet access. Each profile also strengthens your baseline security by changing the default outbound action across all firewall profiles from Allow to Block. As a result, third-party applications must earn your trust before they can connect to the Internet.</value>
  </data>
